name: An ECMS user creates an Accordion component and views it on the General Content page undefined @inw @component

steps.name: Given: I navigate to home page
When: Create a Generic Content page
locator.getByRole('button', { name: 'Open context menu for Home' }).waitFor
locator.getByRole('button', { name: 'Open context menu for Home' }).click
Then: I navigate back to home page
Given: I select a Generic Content page
And: I search for the Accordion component
And: I click the Accordion component
And: I click the Add Accordion Item button (1/4)

And: I click Add content button
                             And: I choose and select Headline component for the accordion entry.
And: I click 'Create' button for Accordion Item
And: I click the Add Accordion Item button (2/4)

And: I click Add content button
                             And: I choose and select Headline component for the accordion entry.
And: I click 'Create' button for Accordion Item
And: I click the Add Accordion Item button (3/4)

And: I click Add content button
                             And: I choose and select Headline component for the accordion entry.
And: I click 'Create' button for Accordion Item
And: I click the Add Accordion Item button (4/4)

And: I click Add content button
                             And: I choose and select Headline component for the accordion entry.
And: I click 'Create' button for Accordion Item

And: I click 'Create' button for Accordion component
                         And: I click 'Save and publish' button

When: I click 'Info' tab
                         And: click the link to the page

And: I redirect the Generic Content page
                         Then: I should see the Accordion displayed on the Generic Content Page with details
